# GSAP Animation Rules

## Setup Requirements
Every file using GSAP must:
1. Have `'use client'` at the top
2. Import gsap and plugins explicitly
3. Register plugins before use

```tsx
'use client'
import { gsap } from 'gsap'
import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger'

gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger)
```

## Always Use gsap.context() for Cleanup
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const ctx = gsap.context(() => {
    // all GSAP code here
  }, containerRef) // scope to a ref

  return () => ctx.revert() // cleanup — always required
}, [])
```

## Prefer Reusable Components
Before writing raw GSAP, check if these components handle the need:
- `<ScrollReveal>` — fade + slide on scroll (up/left/right)
- `<StaggerReveal>` — staggered children reveal on scroll  
- `<AnimatedCounter>` — number count-up on scroll

## Standard Easing
```
power3.out    → standard entrances (most common)
power2.out    → subtle / secondary elements
back.out(1.7) → playful emphasis (use sparingly)
sine.inOut    → infinite loops / oscillation
```

## Standard Durations
```
0.5s  → micro interactions (hover effects)
0.7s  → standard reveals
0.9s  → hero / prominent animations
1.2s+ → very slow / atmospheric (use rarely)
```

## Timeline Pattern for Hero Sections
```tsx
const tl = gsap.timeline({ delay: 0.5 })
tl.fromTo(tagEl,   { opacity: 0, x: -30 }, { opacity: 1, x: 0, duration: 0.6, ease: 'power2.out' })
  .fromTo(titleEl, { opacity: 0, y: 80  }, { opacity: 1, y: 0, duration: 0.9, ease: 'power3.out' }, '-=0.2')
  .fromTo(subEl,   { opacity: 0, y: 20  }, { opacity: 1, y: 0, duration: 0.7               }, '-=0.4')
  .fromTo(ctaEl,   { opacity: 0, y: 20  }, { opacity: 1, y: 0, duration: 0.7               }, '-=0.4')
```

## ScrollTrigger Defaults
```tsx
scrollTrigger: {
  trigger: el,
  start: 'top 88%',   // trigger when top of element reaches 88% of viewport
  toggleActions: 'play none none none',  // play once (forward only)
}
```

## Initial State — Inline Style
When an element needs to start hidden (opacity: 0) before GSAP runs:
```tsx
// Use inline style, NOT Tailwind opacity-0 (Tailwind might override GSAP)
<div ref={ref} style={{ opacity: 0 }}>
```

## NEVER
- ❌ Call GSAP outside of useEffect or event handlers
- ❌ Forget `ctx.revert()` — causes ScrollTrigger leaks
- ❌ Use `document.querySelector` — always use refs
- ❌ Register the same plugin multiple times in the same file
